				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${Z}^{{\prime} }=\frac{R}{1+{(\omega RC)}^{2}},\,\,\,{Z}^{{\prime}{\prime} }=\frac{\omega {R}^{2}C}{1+{(\omega RC)}^{2}}$$\end{document}where R and C are the resistor and capacitor, respectively, and ω is the excitation frequency ω = 2πf, as detailed in the literature54.

